@startuml Deployment Diagram - Cross-Platform Support

title Phase 1.5 & Phase 2 - Cross-Platform Deployment Architecture

!define WINDOWS_COLOR #E3F2FD
!define MACOS_COLOR #F3E5F5
!define LINUX_COLOR #FFF9C4
!define SHARED_COLOR #E8F5E9

node "Windows PC" <<Windows>> WINDOWS_COLOR {
  node "Windows 10/11 x64" as Win10 {
    component "Genshin Impact\n(GenshinImpact.exe)" as GenshinWin
    note bottom: Official client\nWindowed or Fullscreen\n16:9 or 16:10

    artifact "Inventory Kamera\n(WinForms - Phase 1.5)\n(.NET Framework 4.7.2)" as AppWinForms
    note bottom: Current implementation\nWindows-only\nAdapter for Core library

    artifact "Inventory Kamera 2.0\n(Avalonia - Phase 2)\n(.NET 8)" as AppWinAvalonia #LightGray
    note bottom: Future cross-platform UI\nWindows/Linux/macOS

    component "Core Library\n(.NET 8)" as CoreWin SHARED_COLOR
    component "WindowsScreenCapture\n(Graphics.CopyFromScreen)" as WinCapture
    component "WindowsInputSimulator\n(WindowsInput library)" as WinInput
    component "ImageSharp\n(Cross-platform)" as ImageSharpWin SHARED_COLOR
    component "Tesseract 5.x\n(tesseract.dll)" as TesseractWin SHARED_COLOR

    database "ScanProfile.json\ndatasources.json\ninventorylists/*.json" as ConfigWin

    AppWinForms --> CoreWin
    AppWinAvalonia ..> CoreWin : (Phase 2)
    CoreWin --> WinCapture
    CoreWin --> WinInput
    CoreWin --> ImageSharpWin
    CoreWin --> TesseractWin
    CoreWin --> ConfigWin : reads

    WinCapture --> GenshinWin : captures
    WinInput --> GenshinWin : controls
  }
}

node "macOS Machine" <<macOS>> MACOS_COLOR {
  node "macOS Sonoma (M3 Max)" as MacOS #LightGray {
    component "Genshin Impact\n(via Wine/Crossover)" as GenshinMac #LightGray
    note bottom: Unofficial (Wine)\nOr native if/when available

    artifact "Inventory Kamera 2.0\n(Avalonia)\n(.NET 8)" as AppMac #LightGray
    note bottom: Phase 2 only\nNative macOS app

    component "Core Library\n(.NET 8)" as CoreMac SHARED_COLOR
    component "macOSScreenCapture\n(CGWindowListCreateImage)" as MacCapture #LightGray
    component "macOSInputSimulator\n(Core Graphics)" as MacInput #LightGray
    component "ImageSharp\n(Cross-platform)" as ImageSharpMac SHARED_COLOR
    component "Tesseract 5.x\n(libtesseract.dylib)" as TesseractMac SHARED_COLOR

    database "ScanProfile.json\ndatasources.json\ninventorylists/*.json" as ConfigMac

    AppMac --> CoreMac
    CoreMac --> MacCapture
    CoreMac --> MacInput
    CoreMac --> ImageSharpMac
    CoreMac --> TesseractMac
    CoreMac --> ConfigMac : reads

    MacCapture --> GenshinMac : captures
    MacInput --> GenshinMac : controls
  }
}

node "Linux PC / Steam Deck" <<Linux>> LINUX_COLOR {
  node "SteamOS 3.0 / Ubuntu 22.04" as Linux #LightGray {
    component "Genshin Impact\n(via Proton)" as GenshinLinux #LightGray
    note bottom: Official via Steam\nProton compatibility layer

    artifact "Inventory Kamera 2.0\n(Avalonia)\n(.NET 8)" as AppLinux #LightGray
    note bottom: Phase 2 only\nFirst native Linux scanner!

    component "Core Library\n(.NET 8)" as CoreLinux SHARED_COLOR
    component "LinuxScreenCapture\n(X11/Wayland)" as LinuxCapture #LightGray
    component "LinuxInputSimulator\n(xdotool/ydotool)" as LinuxInput #LightGray
    component "ImageSharp\n(Cross-platform)" as ImageSharpLinux SHARED_COLOR
    component "Tesseract 5.x\n(libtesseract.so)" as TesseractLinux SHARED_COLOR

    database "ScanProfile.json\ndatasources.json\ninventorylists/*.json" as ConfigLinux

    AppLinux --> CoreLinux
    CoreLinux --> LinuxCapture
    CoreLinux --> LinuxInput
    CoreLinux --> ImageSharpLinux
    CoreLinux --> TesseractLinux
    CoreLinux --> ConfigLinux : reads

    LinuxCapture --> GenshinLinux : captures
    LinuxInput --> GenshinLinux : controls

    note bottom of Linux
      **Steam Deck Notes:**
      - 1280x800 resolution (16:10)
      - Gaming Mode: Needs desktop mode or overlay
      - Performance: OCR may be slower on Deck
      - ScanProfile: "steam-deck" preset
    end note
  }
}

cloud "GitHub" {
  database "DimbreathBot/AnimeGameData\n(Game data repository)" as GitHub
  note bottom: Fallback repositories:\n- Sycamore0/GenshinData\n- User-configured alternatives
}

CoreWin ..> GitHub : HTTP GET
CoreMac ..> GitHub : HTTP GET
CoreLinux ..> GitHub : HTTP GET

note as SharedNote
  **Shared Components:**
  - Core Library: 100% identical across platforms
  - ImageSharp: Cross-platform image processing
  - Tesseract: Native library per platform
  - Configuration: Same JSON files everywhere

  **Platform-Specific:**
  - Screen capture API
  - Input simulation API
  - Native library names (.dll/.dylib/.so)
end note

CoreWin .. SharedNote
CoreMac .. SharedNote
CoreLinux .. SharedNote

note as DependencyInjection
  **Dependency Injection:**
  Platform detection at runtime:

  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
      services.AddSingleton<IScreenCapture, WindowsScreenCapture>();
  else if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.OSX))
      services.AddSingleton<IScreenCapture, macOSScreenCapture>();
  else if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Linux))
      services.AddSingleton<IScreenCapture, LinuxScreenCapture>();

  Core library never knows which implementation is used!
end note

AppWinAvalonia .. DependencyInjection
AppMac .. DependencyInjection
AppLinux .. DependencyInjection

note as Phase1vs2
  **Phase 1.5 (Current):**
  ✅ Core library extracted
  ✅ Windows implementation only
  ✅ WinForms UI (existing)
  ✅ ScanProfile.json support
  ❌ macOS/Linux not implemented yet

  **Phase 2 (Future):**
  ✅ Avalonia UI (replaces WinForms)
  ✅ macOS implementation
  ✅ Linux implementation
  ✅ Cross-platform deployment
  ✅ Modern, resizable UI
end note

Win10 .. Phase1vs2

@enduml
